title: Tough Road
overview: During a chase of drug deal, officer magdy lost his way in the desert , got saved by Saba. He finds out that saba's family is drug lord and they also identify  him so they decided to kill him but by the help of saba, they escaped.

title: Uczta Baltazara
overview: Engineer Andrzej Uriaszewicz returns to Poland in order to smuggle a valuable painting out of the country.

title: The Great Merlini
overview: A magician is hired to prevent a jewel heist but the diamonds still disappear despite him being near them.

title: Street Bandits
overview: A lawyer (Robert Clarke) defends a slot-machine king, and his bride (Penny Edwards) and partner (Ross Ford) don't like it.

title: Road to crime
overview: A moral parable about juvenile delinquency, which takes a tour of different characters of the Buenos Aires fauna.

title: Riscatto - Tu sei il mio giudice
Road to Crime
overview: In Sao Paulo , young Sergio works in a bank in which her ​​rich uncle is the president. Using his name to borrow money, Sergio takes a wasteful life frequenting nightclubs and dating the sophisticated starlet 's revues Margo. His uncle refuses to pay the loans and Sergio finds himself in difficulties that lead down a dark path.

title: Paco, el elegante
overview: Paco's ordered by a higher-up in his gang to beat up a journalist who wants to write exposes about Mexico City drug traffic, and that ends up opening a whole can of worms.

title: House No. 13
overview: Sherif visits a psychiatrist for his illness who exploits him to commit a murder by hypnotism.

title: The Crime of the Just
overview: Arnal, nicknamed 'Counselor' is the head of a family held in high esteem by the people of a Cevennes village. Now, the dignified man, who is the respected arbitrator of local disputes, has adopted Clémence, a deaf-mute girl. The day when Maurice, Arnal's son, starts a love affair with his stepsister, trouble begins...

title: The Little Woman
overview: A little girl hides a criminal in her playhouse.

title: Amanecer a la vida
overview: A shoeshine boy and his mother, a cabaret employee, fight against life's adversities. Venezuelan drama directed by Fernando Cortés.

title: Correctional
overview: The forthcoming wedding of Norma and Armando, a young lawyer, was supposed to be a great and wonderful event for the two, but everything went haywire.

title: Tåg norrut
overview: The destinies of different kind of people encounter in a passenger train that is traveling from Helsinki to the North.

title: La fuerza ciega
overview: A shipyard owner rapes the daughter of a blind worker, unaware that she is his own son's girlfriend.

title: Skid Kids
overview: Story about a group of young cyclist track riders and their effort to retain their track against long odds.

title: Gilbert Harding Speaking of Murder
overview: lation of 3 stories, "The Missing Passenger", "Falstaff's Fur Coat" and "Thirty Days To Die". Originally part of the Danziger Brothers' UK series "Calling Scotland Yard" and later shown in the US on NBC's "Adventure Theatre" in 1956, hosted by Paul Douglas.

title: Rua sem Sol
overview: A poor girl must find the money to pay for her blind sister's eyesight operation.

title: Recommended capture
overview: Dramatizations of four cases "drawn from Buenos Aires police files".

title: The Drayton Case
overview: During the early years of World War II, a bomb from a German airplane uncovers the corpse of a strangled woman.

title: Vigilantes y ladrones
overview: The "Cinco Grandes del Buen Humor" look for a hidden treasure in the basement of a hotel.

title: Tourbillon
overview: Taking advantage of the shooting of a film, gangsters stage a hold -up. A black man, Selim, is unfairly accused.

title: Crown Jewels
overview: As foreign troops occupy the country, the government commissions a jeweler to bring the crown jewels to safety.

title: Prämien auf den Tod
overview: In order to impress a socially superior woman with money, an unsuccessful insurance agent commits sophisticated fraud: he concludes contracts with fictitious people and collects the insurance sums after their "death". However, his first fictional persona is his downfall.

title: Calling Scotland Yard: Falstaff's Fur Coat
overview: Because of his luxurious fur coat, a hammy actor becomes involved with crooks. His coat resembles the one that a gang's fence wears, and he is continually finding stolen jewelry in his coat pockets. When the gang learns that he is planning to turn the loot over to Scotland Yard, they go gunning for him and wound him while he is on stage performing 'Falstaff.' And, although wounded, he continues with his performance, trouper that he is that believes the show must go on, while the police are apprehending the gunmen.

title: Brutality
overview: When the body of a postman is found on Lake Neusiedl, the investigation shows that it is probably a robbery, and several of the villagers fall into the circle of suspects: Five young men now need an alibi. Walter was with Elisabeth on the night of the murder, but cannot rely on her support. She is not only the sister of Stephan, who is also suspected, but also the fiancée of the gendarme who is leading the investigation into the case.

title: Paapi
overview: On the run from the police, an atheist masquerades as a religious icon.

title: Der gute Onkel
overview: The murder of a child is solved.

title: Lady Pickpocket
overview: A girl who is placed by circumstances in corrupt circumstances, learns the craft of pickpocketing, joins a gang that exploits her work, and after a period of narrowing the life of corruption and hate being in this gang

title: The Shadow of Another
overview: A drama about double personality

title: Heart of the Casbah
overview: Maria-Pilar is the new wife of an Algerian gangster whom the police have just arrested. The son of a first marriage arrives in Algiers from which he has remained far away for a long time. His stepmother, charmed by the teenager, gradually experiences a devouring passion, against which Michel tries in vain to fight: he loves a young girl, Sylvie. Mad with jealousy, his stepmother singles him out for his father's vengeance by distorting the truth. Michel does not escape his father's fury, but when the woman's deception becomes known, Maria-Pilar is strangled to death.

title: Sie kommen immer in der Nacht
The Fugitive
overview: Framed for a killing, a teenager takes refuge in a farm house.

title: The Second Mate
overview: Murderous smugglers kidnap a troublesome Bargemans son in this British crime drama, filmed on the Thames.

title: The Woman with the Orchid
overview: A bold police officer arrives, not without difficulty, to infiltrate a dangerous gang of drug traffickers. With the help of a beautiful young woman, he tries to stop their nefarious activities ...

title: Luz Apagada
overview: On a small coastal town, a light-keeper lives in total seclusion after his wife's passing. His daughter is also there and she becomes his only contact with the other locals, and when a helper is sent to assist him on duties, she asks a childhood friend of hers to marry her, so he can be appointed as her father's helper.

title: Mercado negro
overview: A policeman discovers that his girlfriend's father heads a drug smuggling band.

title: Hell of the Crazy
overview: The adventure of a driver who gets mixed up with heroin smugglers by chance.

title: Greed
overview: A precious pearl necklace is stolen from a dying widow and repeatedly changes hands because many covet it, leaving behind a long trail of blood.

title: Escombros
overview: When cornered by a police lieutenant, Eddie Randall advises the officer that he has a gun, then tells him how he came to this moment: Eddie relocated to New York's Spanish Harlem and was seduced by Rita Felton, who offers him work in her import/export business.

title: Rechter Thomas
overview: Based on the book Rechter Thomas by François Pauwels.

title: Dear Dolly
overview: After her father is arrested for murdering his cousin, a young toddler falls into the hand of two lower class men who do everything in their power to reunite her with family members.

title: Mayakanan
overview: The story follows two friends, Mohan and Bhola, who stumble upon a mysterious garden house called "Mayakanan." The house is owned by Dr. Naresh Ray, a wealthy scientist with a dark secret. When Ray sets his sights on Shanta, Mohan's fiancée, he resorts to sinister tactics to win her over.

title: Candidate for Murder
overview: Amateur film by Don Coleman, made in the '50s using an original script by Oswell Blakeston. Filmed at various locations in London. Not to be confused with another amateur production of the same script, made by one Sidney B. Shenker.
